<h4>Applying Fonts</h4>

<p>Choosing the font for the text of your document means choosing what the
characters you type will look like. There are many, many options from which to
choose. In selecting the font, you choose not only the font but also the size.
Default font size is usually a 10 or 12.</p>

<p>To explore fonts, open a Word document and type some lines of text.
Highlight your text and from the toolbar at the top of your document, look for
the box with the font name. Each font has its own name, such as "Times New 
Roman", "Arial"ù, "Lucida Sans"ù and "Verdana"ù. Click on the arrow
to reveal the pull down <strong>font menu</strong> and select the desired font. Notice they are listed in alphabetical order. Then select the desired size from the font size from the pull down arrow.</p>					
<p>The toolbars look slightly different for each version of Microsoft Word, so familiarize yourself with your version.</p>


