<h4>Text Effects</h4>

<p>You may choose a variety of text effects to apply to the text in your document.<p> 

<p>Text effects are different from the font. The font is how the characters look when you type them out and each font is unique and different. The styles and effects can be applied to text in all fonts and do the same thing to the text no matter what the font.</p>


<h5>Bold, Italics, and Underline</h5>

<p>Common examples of text effects are <strong>bold</strong>, <i>italics</i>, and <u>underline</u>. You can apply the most common of effects by highlighting the text and then choosing an icon from the toolbar at the top of your document.</p>

<p>Once again, the toolbars look slightly different for each version of Microsoft Word, so familiarize yourself with your version.</p>



